00:29:04.800 --> 00:29:13.340
2.7 time 10 to the 4 pascals.

00:29:13.340 --> 00:29:17.900
So let's just calculate, given
this small additional pressure,

00:29:17.900 --> 00:29:20.860
how high is the
liquid going to go,

00:29:20.860 --> 00:29:26.380
above the level of the solution.

00:29:26.380 --> 00:29:28.080
Anybody want to guess?

00:29:28.080 --> 00:29:29.460
You know, a centimeter.

00:29:29.460 --> 00:29:30.430
10 centimeters.

00:29:30.430 --> 00:29:32.040
100 centimeters?

00:29:32.040 --> 00:29:33.520
Give me an order of magnitude.

00:29:33.520 --> 00:29:35.700
Who guesses one centimeter?

00:29:35.700 --> 00:29:36.690
You got three choices.

00:29:36.690 --> 00:29:39.040
One, 10 and 100, and
you have to make one.

00:29:39.040 --> 00:29:41.250
Who guesses one centimeter?

00:29:41.250 --> 00:29:43.040
Who guesses 10 centimeters?

00:29:43.040 --> 00:29:46.020
Who guesses 100 centimeters?

00:29:46.020 --> 00:29:49.260
OK.

00:29:49.260 --> 00:29:53.520
Now, fortunately we
don't do problem sets.

00:29:53.520 --> 00:29:58.320
Or other scientific
problems by popular vote.

00:29:58.320 --> 00:29:59.830
Rather, we just solve them.

00:29:59.830 --> 00:30:01.500
Whenever possible.

00:30:01.500 --> 00:30:15.030
So, what's the height
of a column of solution?

00:30:15.030 --> 00:30:22.050
Well, that pi, remember, that's
equal to rho times g times h,

00:30:22.050 --> 00:30:22.830
right?

00:30:22.830 --> 00:30:24.520
And we know pi now.

00:30:24.520 --> 00:30:30.240
So h is pi over rho times g.

00:30:30.240 --> 00:30:36.410
So it's 2.7 times
10 to the 4 pascal

00:30:36.410 --> 00:30:43.870
over rho, that's 0.995
grams per centimeters cubed.

00:30:43.870 --> 00:30:56.010
Times 1 kilogram over 1000 grams
times 100 centimeters per meter

00:30:56.010 --> 00:30:56.510
cubed.

00:30:56.510 --> 00:30:58.670
I'm just getting
this into units that

00:30:58.670 --> 00:31:01.350
will give me, that
will be in meters,

00:31:01.350 --> 00:31:06.280
times 9.8 meter per
a second squared.

00:31:06.280 --> 00:31:13.230
And when I multiply all
